  • Method Details

    • canBiometricAuthenticate

      int canBiometricAuthenticate()
      Indicates if the provided authenticators is supported and configured on the device.
      Returns:
      integer which indicates if the provided authenticator can be used.

      Possible values:

      • BiometricAuthenticationStatus.BIO_AUTHENTICATION_SUCCESS: One of the requested authenticators can be used (enrolled and available).
      • BiometricAuthenticationStatus.BIOMETRIC_NO_HARDWARE: No biometric hardware in the device.
      • BiometricAuthenticationStatus.BIOMETRIC_HW_UNAVAILABLE: None of the authenticators are currently supported/enabled.
      • BiometricAuthenticationStatus.BIOMETRIC_NOT_ENROLLED: None of the requested authenticators are enrolled.
      Since:
      5.4.0

    • updateDeviceFingerprintSource

      void updateDeviceFingerprintSource(@NonNull String tokenName, @Nullable byte[] oldCustomFingerprintData, @NonNull MobileFingerprintSource newFingerprintSource) throws FastTrackException
      Apply the new device fingerprint source for the token. This API will help to change (add or remove) the device fingerprint source.

      NOTE:

      • The application manages the custom fingerprint data value so that it uses the proper value while retrieving the token device, for example, by calling CapMobileProtector.getTokenDevice(String, byte[])
      • The application has to retrieve the token device again to update the changes.
      Parameters:
      tokenName - The token name
      oldCustomFingerprintData - The old custom fingerprint data (if any)
      newFingerprintSource - The new fingerprint source
      Throws:
      FastTrackException - If the updating fails, possible result code:
      • FastTrackException.DEVICE_FINGERPRINT if the provided oldCustomFingerprintData does not match with the one while creating the token. Especially, the code FastTrackException.DEVICE_FINGERPRINT_IDENTICAL will be thrown if the old and new fingerprint source are identical.
      • FastTrackException.INTERNAL_ERROR for any other error
      Since:
      5.4.0
